  %h2.am-margin-top-sm Description
  %p.am-margin-bottom-xl T4 DNA Ligase catalyzes the formation of a phosphodiester bond between juxtaposed 5' phosphate and 3' hydroxyl termini in duplex DNA or RNA. With the optimized reaction buffer, the enzyme can ligate DNA sticky or blunt end fragments as well as repair single-stranded nicks in duplex DNA and some DNA/RNA hybrids. 
